HEADWORD: Glycolyl
<hw>Gly"co*lyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Glycol</ets>ic + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A divalent, compound radical, <chform>CO.CH2</chform>, regarded as
the essential radical of glycolic acid, and a large series of related
compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
